title: The First Episode
description: Book editor Martin Tupper doesn't want to admit his marriage is over.

title: Death Takes a Coffee Break
description: Can book editor Martin Tupper's day get any worse? It starts with a dose from an exterminator at 6:30AM, then losing his coat in a cab door, and progresses to being assaulted by a zoftig female author whose book he rejected. His pal Eddie fixes him up with a amorous 20 year old, but movie-mad Martin ends up in an ER.

title: 555-HELL
description: Bored after breaking up with Nina, Martin is phoning anybody and everybody, when he accidentally takes a call meant for the suicide helpline. The caller is Irma, who he somehow persuades not to 'do the deed', while his apartment is filling up with his associates. Then they leave! This may not be the most entertaining plot summary in the world but it IS what happens.

title: The Second Greatest Story Ever Told
Calling the Kettle Black
description: Martin finds a joint in Jeremy's room.

title: No, I'm Just Happy to See You
To Have and Have and Have and Have Not
Pants on Fire
description: Martin admits having an affair; Jeremy takes disastrous advice on how to play spin the bottle.

title: The Name of the Game Is Five-Card Stud
So Funny I Forgot to Laugh
And Bimbo Was His Name-O Part I
And Bimbo Was His Name-O Part II
For Richard or for Poorer
description: Martin coughs up a kidney for Richard.. for Judith.

title: Come and Knock on Our Door...
Martin Over Medium
description: Martin worries when a young coworker dies. He goes to a psychic to get a prediction of his death. While under hypnosis he has a vision of a previous life where he was a woman and worried her husband was going to die. He sees himself as a man on death row. He keeps going back to the psychic until he sees a vision of himself living.

title: Theory of Relativity
description: Martin sees his baby cousin for the first time in years and she's all grown up. Their elderly aunt catches them kissing and has a mild heart attack. She tells them she had similar feelings and reminds the kids to not act on them.

title: Up All Night
description: Martin is ready to leave the office on Friday afternoon when he finds out a writer's wife has shredded a book, due at the printers on Monday morning. He, the writer, and Toby spend all weekend putting it back together, and get on each others nerves in the process. The writer stands up to his abusive wife and falls for Toby as well. Martin gives up a date with a gorgeous Swedish blonde and fantasizes about her the whole time. When the wife catches all of them at work she destroys the book again. Martin contemplates suicide.

title: The Guilty Party
description: Martin insists on throwing Eddie a bachelor party, despite the protests of Eddie himself and most everyone else. It goes poorly with everyone not drinking or enjoying themselves, until the stripper arrives. Then it gets even worse.

title: The Son Also Rises
description: Martin is missing condoms and learns Jeremy is starting to grow up. Judith seems calm until it finally strikes home he might actually have sex.

title: It Came from Beneath the Sink
No Deposit, No Return
description: An old friend asks Martin for his sperm so she can have a baby. When he starts to develop feelings for the baby she has to remind him what his place is.

title: To the Moon, Alex!
description: A new guy at the publishing house threatens to destroy Martin with underhanded moves, until he enlists friends to fight back.

title: Oral Sex, Lies and Videotape
description: While filming his son out on the streets Martin accidentally catches a beloved child entertainer receiving services from a street walker. He confronts the star in his dressing room in an effort to get him to clean up his act. The man offers his penis instead. In anger, Martin sells the tape to his pal Eddie to run on his show. Once the hooker incident is made public, the entertainer throws himself off a building. Martin meets the daughter in an effort to console her pain. He confesses his role in the expose, and she sues him. They go to trial where all of Martins mis-deeds are put under the public eye. He settles only to find out the daughter always knew that a hit man had actually killed her father.

title: The French Conception
description: Martin's old girlfriend Julie comes to him looking for payment for an abortion. Martin is trying to sell his old apartment, now that he's living with Julie's mom.

title: Depth Be Not Proud
description: Eddie loses his job as a talk show host. Martin tries to cheer him up by offering to start a magazine together. Martin works too hard on the project and when Gibby calls him on it, they fight and Martin quits. Eddie gets a job as a morning talk show host and quits on the magazine. Martin goes crawling back for his job.

title: Pop Secret
description: Martin's dad visits New York after his divorce. He goes on a date with Toby's mom but nothing happens. Martin is suspicious and goes to see him at Roger's house. While there he notices the lack of space for two people and begins to wonder if his dad is gay. He eventually confronts his father and learns the truth.

title: Reach Out and Touch Yourself
description: When Martin finds some old savings bonds he decides to reinvest the money. Toby convinces him to start her phone stock tips business but it does poorly. She gets inspiration to change it to a phone sex line, of which Martin disapproves.

title: Home Sweet Homeboy
description: Eddie tries to get in touch with his black roots after an incident on his talk show. Martin tries to support him but finds it a little annoying.

title: A Midsummer Night's Dream On
description: Martin, Eddie and Judith spend a weekend at a cabin with their old college friends. Passions spark and secrets are revealed. Martin fusses over a 20 year old misdeed.

title: The Book, the Thief, Her Boss and His Lover
Super Freak
description: Martin falls for his sexy superintendent during a New York heat wave. When the passion fizzles he tries to dump her, with disastrous results to his utilities.

title: One Ball, Two Strikes
description: Martin is irritated about having to attend a crummy office party. He meets a gorgeous blonde and she jumps his bones. Later that night he learns its actually Gibby's girlfriend. The next morning Gibby tells Martin he suspects the girlfriend of cheating on him and confesses it may be due to his missing testicle. When Gibby eventually learns its because he's a great big jerk he no longer has a problem with it.

title: Portrait by the Artist on the Young Man
description: Jeremy shows up with a tattoo on his arm. Martin disapproves angrily while Judith displays a more rational response. The two men fight and eventually Judith gives in to the suggestion of having it removed.

title: And Bobby Makes Three
description: While helping Judith attend a Lamaze class, Martin sees an old girlfriend and starts up a new relationship. Things seem to be going well until her baby's daddy shows up at the door.

title: Silent Night, Holy Cow Part I
description: Martin gets roped into taking Judith around on Christmas while her husband is in Rome. Toby sees the Virgin Mary in his broken glass. Eddie tries to juggle multiple girlfriends and spends Christmas alone. Jeremy has sex for the first time and it doesn't go so well. Martin and Judith cant get a room in town and end up stuck in the snow when her water breaks.

title: Silent Night, Holy Cow Part II
Brother of the Bride
description: Martins sister Susan calls up to announce she's eloping and she wants him (and only him) at the wedding. Martin spills the beans to his curmudgeonly, gay father, who somehow gets the word around town to his mom. Eventually they get all their friends and family to attend, much to Susans dismay.

title: Blinded by the Cheese
description: Martin gets blinded by hot cheese fondue and ends up in the hospital. A sexy nurse takes pity on him and eventually they have an affair. When his bandages are removed he is surprised to find she's considerably older than he is. They try dating but Martin cant get images of grandma out of his mind. She dumps him when he is caught checking out young gals at the gym.

title: The Taking of Pablum 1-2-3: Part I
The Taking of Pablum 1-2-3: Part II
'Tis Pity She's a Neighbor
description: Martin's new neighbor makes an awful lot of noise in bed. One night when he's had enough he goes over to complain and finds a gorgeous brunette at the door. She claims the noise is her roommate. Martin asks her over to his place for coffee and they end up having wild passionate sex. In the morning Martin learns the horrible truth.

title: Steinway to Heaven
description: When Martin's mother passes away unexpectedly, he finds himself with a beat up old piano and a quest to fulfill her last wishes.

title: I'm with Stupid
description: Martin isn't happy with his current girlfriends brain, so he finds a new one smarter than him, which proves to be even more stressful and intimidating.

title: I Never Promised You Charoses, Martin
description: Jeremy decides to embrace Christianity much to Martins distress. He tries to introduce him to Judaism at Judith's dinner party but it ends up causing a family feud.

title: The Courtship of Martin's Father
description: Martins dad breaks up with his old boyfriend and decides to move in with Martin. The stress of living with is father prompts Martin to take him to a gay bar and find some companionship. Martins father meets Martins current book author and the two hit it off, forcing Martin to intervene when gay overtones threaten to take over the book.

title: Try Not to Remember
description: Martin has difficulty in bed and goes to a psychiatrist to learn he was molested as a child.

title: Bess You Is Not My Woman Now
description: An old friend comes back to New York and Martin thinks she's interested in him. What he doesnt know is she actually wants to meet Judith.

title: Long Distance Runaround
description: Eddie moves to Hollywood for work and Martin realizes they cant be long distance friends. He finds another buddy back in New York right around the time Eddie gets fired.

title: Significant Author
description: Desperate for a hit book, Martin signs up a well known author only to find out the man's next work is Toby Pedalbee.

title: 9 1/2 Days
description: One of Martins seemingly uptight writers turns out to be a closet sex addict. Things get strange for him when she asks to have another woman join them.

title: Take Two Tablets, and Get Me to Mt. Sinai
Music in My Veins: Part I
Music in My Veins: Part II
Tie Me Sister Lu Down, Sport
She Won't Do It, But Her Sister Will
Home Is Where the Cart Is
The Weekend at the College Didn't Turn Out Like They Planned
